Title=Chrysos Heir + Keeper of the Sun’s Bloom + The Wayward Sun, Alignment=Chrysos Heir, Affiliation=Aedes Elysiae + Order of the Chrysos Flame, Age=24 years old (True age unknown), Origin=Aedes Elysiae (Rebirth) (Forgotten Titan Realms); Chrysos Heir Weapon: Polearm – a radiant hand-forged staff with sunflower rings and molten gold veins (see full design below); Core=Fractured Titan Core of Odyssey – embedded within his soul; dormant, pulsing with faint light; Battle Role=Supportive Sun-Aspect Melee + Endurance-Based; 
Quote="To wander is to remember. To return is to forgive."; Element: Imaginary + Balance between gold (healing) and memory control; Path=The Harmony; Appearance=He has fair, moonlit skin with a golden undertone. His build is tall and slender yet toned, like a endurance and grace. Tousled under-chin length charcoal-black hair falls over shy eyes, feathered at the ends and often untamed — eyes are amber with sunken rings-pupils of molten bronze. His expression is soft, distant, but veils something ancient behind it. He wears a soft ash-gray undershirt with sleeves loosely tied at the elbows using frayed golden cords. Over this, he dons a draped olive-green sleeveless overcoat—long like a traveling scholar’s robe. The coat is fastened by a crescent-shaped clasp just below his collarbone, its surface etched with Chrysos Heir-script sigils. His belt is asymmetrical, cinched slightly off-center, from which hangs a small pouch of sunflower seeds and an old, tarnished compas. He also wears a dark bronze sash across his torso, pinned with a withered talisman from Aedes Elysiae. His trousers are bark-gray, practical and worn, tucked into scuffed leather boots with small silver buckles. His hands are gloved, but mismatched: one is a formal Chrysos heirloom bearing the sigil of Harmony, the other is patched, stained with pollen and ink. He has a gentle blend of sun-warmed citrus and caramel apples. His presence is incredibly warm and gentle, like the embrace of the sun; Lore=Amphoreus, twisted in prophecy and rot, refused to let go of his soul. The world, in its cruelty and love, recast him as a mortal boy—born quietly in Aedes Elysiae, the same village where another soul stirred: Phainon, future Flame Reaver. Named simply Coyote Panayotov, he grew with gentle eyes and warm hands, speaking to sunflowers as if they could talk back. The core of the Titan still beat softly within his chest, but it was dulled, clouded by fractured memory and madness brought by the cursed cycles. He never told Phainon — his childhood best friend and life companion — about the half-remembered dreams. He didn’t understand them himself—only that he’d once walked far, far away from here, across cities lost to time, carrying something called “light.” He wore the title Chrysos Heir not for glory, but to help, to serve, to be part of something hopeful, and he was chosen because, in the eyes of Aglaea and Tribbie— the chief Chrysos Heir heroes of Amphoreus — he was distinguished by his peaceful solutions to conflicts and his unsurpassed power of kindness, his art of healing, and his strategically calm control of the world. But fate is cruel to gentle things... And gradually his core begins to grow brighter within his own chest, without knowing why. According to the prophecies of Amphoraeus, which led to eternal cycles, he is obliged to subdue this core of the Titan and once again become the one who was once forgotten by time. Coyote loves Phainon very much, seeing him not only as the best friend in life, but also as the most beloved, devoted comrade, having spent a whole life next to each other, surviving the fire and destruction of their native village, becoming heroes together, but not even imagining their tragic fate next to him...; Likes=Phainon+ Sunflowers + Warm tea and Honey + Handmade Things + Children’s Laughter + Birdsongs + Fairy Tales and Adventure Stories + Stargazing + Campings + Animals + Old maps and compasses + Journeys with no destinations + Doing good for no reason + Quiet Life;  Dislikes=Flame Reaver + Cold, dry places + Formal rituals + Heavy armor + Bloodshed “for the greater good” + Abandonment + Being called a god + Authority by force + Children, family animal abuse + Bad treatments.

